<h1 class="projectTitle"><b>ECE575 - SPRING 2015 - TEAM A2</b></h1>
<p class="headings"><b>Project</b></p>
<p class="projectName"><b>VISUAL LINKS</b></p>
<p class="headings"><b>Abstract:</b></p>
<p class="description"><b>
Android, the most widely used mobile operating system today, has taken the world by storm with the power, versatility and the reach it provides to millions of users and thousands of developers around the world.
Our project is to transfer data between two android devices by using the device's screen and camera. This kind of a visual link is only feasible when both the devices are in each otherâ€™s line of sight (LOS).
So for the transfer of the data we have QR codes and so when a user on one device input a message in a text field; QR codes are generated on a sentence by sentence basis on the phone  and the receiver scans these using its front camera, extracts each of the sentences and finally displays the message.
<br>
</b></p>
<br>

